At 9:01 PM -0700 10/15/12, Gary Gibson wrote:
>Hi Otmar,
>	The old school solenoids need to be taken apart to clean up. 
>Like, de-solder the wires to the electrical connections, unscrew the 
>top and the clean and maybe replace/clean the copper contacts. The 
>later solenoids have a "fall out" plunger and the top is crimped 
>with no screws. No easy entry. These can be repaired but you'll need 
>to break into the crimp to fix the interior. The plunger will fall 
>out once the solenoid is removed from the starter on "newer" VWs . 
>That is easy to clean.  I've seen the later ones de-crimped and 
>fixed. I suppose it does not need to be pretty.
>	I think that Kevin's starter has a cruddy starter solenoid?  Gary


